      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(session-memory): skip transcript-only assistant rows",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nSession-memory summaries can duplicate assistant replies when a transcript contains both the real provider assistant message and an OpenClaw transcript-only bookkeeping assistant row with identical visible text, such as `delivery-mirror` or `gateway-injected`. Those bookkeeping rows should not be rendered into memory summaries as user-visible assistant turns.\n\n## Summary\n\n- skips OpenClaw delivery-mirror and gateway-injected assistant transcript rows when rendering recent session content for bundled session-memory\n- keeps the real provider assistant response while excluding transcript-only bookkeeping rows\n- adds regression coverage for delivery-mirror and gateway-injected rows\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `npx vitest run src/hooks/bundled/session-memory/handler.test.ts` passes on the rebased PR branch: 1 file, 26 tests\n- regression coverage verifies the real assistant reply renders once while a matching `delivery-mirror` row is skipped\n- regression coverage verifies `gateway-injected` assistant rows are skipped while the real provider row is kept\n\n## Context\n\nRaw transcripts can include both a real assistant response and an OpenClaw bookkeeping assistant row with identical visible text. The session-memory renderer was treating both as normal assistant replies, which duplicated assistant text in memory summaries.",
